<div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center mb-4">
  <h1 class="h3 mb-0"><i class="bi bi-broadcast-pin me-2"></i>Monitoring Location Types</h1>
  <a href="/admin" class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm"><i class="bi bi-arrow-left me-1"></i>Back</a>
</div>

<div class="alert alert-info mb-4">
  <h6 class="fw-bold mb-2"><i class="bi bi-info-circle me-1"></i>Adding a new type requires changes in the network map app</h6>
  <p class="mb-2">Each Monitoring Location Type needs a corresponding icon set, CSS class, and layer group in the network map app. For a new type named <strong>MyType</strong>, complete all three steps below:</p>

  <div class="mb-3">
    <strong>Step 1 — Add icon image files</strong><br>
    <span class="text-muted small">Location: <code>&lt;networkmap&gt;/src/frontend/images/icons/</code></span>
    <div class="mt-1 small">Add three PNG files (one per alert status). The filename must be the type name in <strong>lowercase</strong>:
      <ul class="mb-0 mt-1">
        <li><code>mytype_green.png</code> — all devices OK</li>
        <li><code>mytype_yellow.png</code> — partial alert</li>
        <li><code>mytype_red.png</code> — full alert</li>
      </ul>
      Recommended size: match existing icons (32×32 px). Existing icons: <code>tower_*.png</code>, <code>psap_*.png</code>.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-3">
    <strong>Step 2 — Add a CSS shape class</strong><br>
    <span class="text-muted small">File: <code>&lt;networkmap&gt;/src/frontend/style.css</code></span>
    <div class="mt-1 small">Add a <code>.custom-icon-MyType</code> class in the <em>"Shape per locType"</em> section (around line 24). Use <code>border-radius</code> or <code>clip-path</code> to give the legend dot a distinct shape:
<pre class="bg-body-secondary rounded p-2 mt-1 mb-0">.custom-icon-MyType {
  border-radius: 4px; /* rounded square, adjust as needed */
}</pre>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-0">
    <strong>Step 3 — Add a layer group and routing</strong><br>
    <span class="text-muted small">File: <code>&lt;networkmap&gt;/src/frontend/index.html</code></span>
    <div class="mt-1 small">
      <ol class="mb-0">
        <li>After the existing <code>psapLayer</code> declaration (~line 131), add:<br>
<pre class="bg-body-secondary rounded p-2 mt-1 mb-1">const myTypeLayer = L.layerGroup(); // set .addTo(map) if visible by default
overlayMaps["MyTypes"] = myTypeLayer;</pre>
        </li>
        <li>In the <code>if (site.locType === "Tower") ... else if (site.locType === "PSAP")</code> block (~line 300), add a new <code>else if</code> branch before the fallback:
<pre class="bg-body-secondary rounded p-2 mt-1 mb-0">} else if (site.locType === "MyType") {
  myTypeLayer.addLayer(m);
}</pre>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="row g-4">
  <div class="col-md-4">
    <div class="card shadow-sm">
      <div class="card-header" id="formTitle">Add Monitoring Location Type</div>
      <div class="card-body">
        <form action="/admin/monitoring-location-types" method="POST" id="itemForm">
          <input type="hidden" name="id" id="itemID" value="" />
          <div class="mb-3">
            <label class="form-label">Name <span class="text-danger">*</span></label>
            <input type="text" name="name" id="itemName" class="form-control" required maxlength="100" />
          </div>
          <div class="d-flex gap-2">
            <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-sm" id="submitBtn">Add</button>
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm d-none" id="cancelBtn">Cancel</button>
          </div>
        </form>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-8">
    <div class="card shadow-sm">
      <div class="table-responsive">
        <table class="table table-sm table-hover mb-0">
          <thead><tr><th>Name</th><th>Status</th><th></th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <% items.forEach(t => { %>
            <tr class="<%= t.IsActive ? '' : 'text-muted' %>">
              <td><%= t.TypeName %></td>
              <td><span class="badge <%= t.IsActive ? 'bg-success' : 'bg-secondary' %>"><%= t.IsActive ? 'Active' : 'Inactive' %></span></td>
              <td class="text-end">
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-primary py-0 me-1 js-edit"
                  data-id="<%= t.LocationTypeID %>" data-name="<%= t.TypeName %>">
                  <i class="bi bi-pencil"></i>
                </button>
                <form action="/admin/monitoring-location-types" method="POST" class="d-inline">
                  <input type="hidden" name="id" value="<%= t.LocationTypeID %>" />
                  <input type="hidden" name="action" value="toggle" />
                  <button type="submit" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-secondary py-0"><%= t.IsActive ? 'Disable' : 'Enable' %></button>
                </form>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <% }) %>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<script>
document.querySelectorAll('.js-edit').forEach(function(btn) {
  btn.addEventListener('click', function() {
    document.getElementById('itemID').value   = this.dataset.id;
    document.getElementById('itemName').value = this.dataset.name;
    document.getElementById('formTitle').textContent = 'Edit Monitoring Location Type';
    document.getElementById('submitBtn').textContent = 'Save Changes';
    document.getElementById('cancelBtn').classList.remove('d-none');
    document.getElementById('itemName').focus();
  });
});
document.getElementById('cancelBtn').addEventListener('click', function() {
  document.getElementById('itemForm').reset();
  document.getElementById('itemID').value = '';
  document.getElementById('formTitle').textContent = 'Add Monitoring Location Type';
  document.getElementById('submitBtn').textContent = 'Add';
  this.classList.add('d-none');
});
</script>
